CPDateHelper

A Cappuccino / Objective-J helper class that extends the functionality of CPDate.

This class provides date formatting methods similar to PHP's date() function.



=== INSTALLATION ===

- Place the CPDateHelper.j file in your Cappuccino application directory and include it in your app using @import "CPDateHelper.j"



=== USAGE ===

- Provide a datetime string that's compatible with the JavaScript Date() class.
	ex. @"Wed Aug 5 2009 12:00:00"
	
- Provide a formatting parameter string.
	ex. @"D M jS Y g:i A"

- CPDateHelper returns a formatted CPString.


=== EXAMPLE ===

var date = [CPDateHelper date:@"Wed Aug 5 2009 13:00:00" withFormat:@"D M jS Y g:i A"];
// returns Wed Aug 5th 2009 1:00 PM



=== MORE INFO ===

see PHP's date() function information page for a list of parameters and their return values at http://www.php.net/date